General Information
===================

Gaupol is a subtitle editor for text-based subtitles. Currently supported
formats include SubRip and MicroDVD. Gaupol is in early development stage and
does not yet contain any advanced features. The aim is to make a simple, but
powerful, subtitle editor for multiple subtitle formats.

Current features:

	- Support for a wide range of character encodings
	- Convenient translating
	- Text formatting
	- Gnome HIG 2.0 compliant user interface

Gaupol is released under the GNU General Public License (GPL), see the file
"COPYING" for details.

The official web site is:

	http://home.gna.org/gaupol


Requirements
============

Gaupol should run on any UNIX-like (Linux, BSD, etc.) operating system.
On other operating systems, you can try it to see if it works.

Required:

	- Python >= 2.4
	- PyGTK (with libglade support) >= 2.6

Optional:

	- Psyco, for best results >= 1.4


Running Gaupol
==============

Gaupol can be run either (1) directly from the source directory or (2) it can
be installed to a selected location.

(1) In the source directory, execute the command

	./gaupol

(2) See the file "INSTALL".
